6:
Tis a grand day indeed! I can feel the 
warmth of the sun down to me bones!
9:
Truly, the perfect day for a good walk! 
What better way is there to maintain 
a healthy body? None, I'd reckon!
14: Are you serious about this, Alk?
17:
I know. But I'm not sure when to 
interject.
24:
Oho! Is it that time already? 
I can hardly wait!
36:
It's been centuries since I've had such 
a fine meal!
42:
Huh? Oh, er—I was just wondering... 
can you actually taste anything?
51: S-sorry... But aren't you curious too?
57: I admit it is an enigma to me as well...
62:
Ohoho! It's only natural to be curious. 
Truth be told...
65:
I can't taste a thing! In fact, I have no 
stomach to hold all this food!
72:
Then where does it all go? Do it just fall 
on the floor?
76:
Heavens, no! I would never do 
something so uncouth!
78:
The chippies that reside in me eat any 
food I consume.
86:
Then does that mean... you couldn't 
taste anything after all?
89:
Aye... But it's not quite that simple, 
lassie.
92:
The chippies react in all sorts of ways 
to the things they eat, such as when 
something's spicy or sweet, bitter or 
noxious.
94:
I observe those reactions and 
interpret them as though they were 
me own senses—and that includes 
taste!
98:
H-huh... So it's not the flavor you're 
tasting, but the vibe, basically?
101:
That's a solid understanding of the 
principles. However, my feel more real 
and precise than you may imagine.
102:
Take this soup, for instance. It uses 
a broth made from red mushrooms 
found in me forest, yes?
108: That's so specific... and so accurate!
111:
What's more, I believe you're using... 
ragwort as your secret ingredient?
117:
Y-you could tell?! No one was 
supposed to know about that...
121:
What the hell are you putting in our 
lunches?
125:
Tis a right savory dish you've created, 
but perhaps it could use some spice 
to liven up the flavor!
133:
You're sayin' it's savory, but how do 
we know your sense of taste is the 
same as ours?
137:
Wait, Nimbus—he's absolutely right! 
What this soup needs... is pepper!
144:
Hahaha! Your skepticism is well-
founded, I assure you.
146:
Which begs the question—how can 
we be sure that anyone's sense of 
taste is the same?
150:
That's true. You being a cat, you can't 
handle hot food, right?
157:
Such differences are easy enough to 
uncover among individuals. But doing 
so is uncouth and misses the point!
160:
If anything's for certain, it's that this 
soup is delicious and that Alk is 
a great chef for making it. 
Surely we can all agree on that?
164:
Hear, hear! If a fellow so savory as 
yourself says so, it must be true!
168:
Aha! Don't think I didn't see what you 
did there, champion!
178:
Um... I think it's best if we just let the 
two of them do their thing together.
